$$
\begin{aligned}
& m g=\rho_w \frac{v}{3} g=\rho_A \frac{v}{2} g \ldots \text { (i) } \\
& \rho_{\text {mixure }}=\frac{\rho_w v_0+\rho_A v_0}{2 v_0}=\frac{\rho_w+\rho_A}{2} \\
& m g=\left[\frac{\rho_w+\rho_A}{2}\right] \times\left[\frac{v}{n}\right] g \ldots \text { (ii) }
\end{aligned}
$$

From equation (i) \& (ii) $\rho_w \frac{v}{3} g=\frac{v g}{2 n}\left[\rho_w+\frac{2 \rho_w}{3}\right] ; \frac{1}{3}=\frac{1}{2 n}\left[\frac{5}{3}\right] \Rightarrow n=\frac{5}{2}$
